STR_HS_RAIL                       : High Speed Line (1435 mm)
STR_BUILD_CAPTION                 : New Highspeed (1435 mm) trains
STR_NEW_TRAIN                     : highspeed
STR_HSRAIL_NAME                   : Construction of Highspeed Line 
STR_HSRAIL_TOOLBAR                : Highspeed Line Construction
STR_HSRAIL_DEPOT                  : New Highspeed trains

STR_WAGON_SPEED_NAME              : Freight wagons speed
STR_WAGON_SPEED_DESC              : Selects the speed of freight wagons
STR_WAGON_SPEED_SLOW              : Slow (60, 100, 140).
STR_WAGON_SPEED_DEFAULT           : Default (70, 110, 150).
STR_WAGON_SPEED_FAST              : Fast (80, 120, 160).
STR_WAGON_SPEED_MAX               : Extreme speed (110, 160, 220).
STR_PROTOTYPES_AVAILABLE_NAME     : Availability of prototype trains.
STR_PROTOTYPES_AVAILABLE_DESC     : Select the availability of prototype trains.
STR_NO_PROTOTYPES                 : No prototypes.
STR_PROTOTYPES                    : Prototypes available.
STR_PROTOTYPES_LIFESPAN_NAME      : Lifespan of prototype trains.
STR_PROTOTYPES_LIFESPAN_DESC      : Select the lifespan of prototype trains.
STR_LOW_LIFESPAN_PROTOTYPES       : Prototypes have a low lifespan (between 8 and 15 years)
STR_NORMAL_LIFESPAN_PROTOTYPES    : Prototypes have a similar lifespan than other trains (between 20 and 40 years)
STR_HSTRAINS_TRACK_NAME           : Track type of high-speed trains.
STR_HSTRAINS_TRACK_DESC           : Select the track type of high-speed trains (for compatibility with other NewGRF's). Note that making high speed trains running in default electric rail may turn useless some electric trains.
STR_ELRL                          : High speed trains run on Default Electric Rail type like the other trains.
STR_HSRL                          : High speed trains run on special high-speed tracks (default option)
STR_TRAIN_COST_NAME               : Purchase cost of trains.
STR_TRAIN_COST_DESC               : Select the purchase cost of trains. For example, with the default value, a high speed train costs about 1M €. With low value, it only costs 500K€. With high value it will cost almost 2M €.
STR_WAGON_COST_NAME               : Purchase cost of wagons.
STR_WAGON_COST_DESC               : Select the purchase cost of wagons. Wagons cost near 2500€ with low prices and near 10000€ with high prices.
STR_RUNNING_COST_NAME             : Running cost of trains.
STR_RUNNING_COST_DESC             : Select the running cost of trains.
STR_COST_LOW                      : The cost is low. Best for recreating networks without having to worry about money.
STR_COST_MEDIUM                   : The cost is medium. Default option.
STR_COST_HIGH                     : The cost is high. Best if you're looking for a challenge.